title: ‘Inventing terminology’: Macpherson accuses police of ‘lying to the public’ about school shooting
description: Sky News host James Macpherson accuses authorities of using misleading terminology following a fatal school shooting in Canada.  “Lying to the public about what constitutes a woman reached ridiculous levels last week after a school shooting in Canada,” Mr Macpherson said.  “Astute observers, by which I mean anyone with a brain, knew something was up when police confirmed that one of the nine people killed was Gunperson?  “Police were literally inventing terminology to disguise the truth of what actually occurred at Tumbler Ridge Secondary School.  “They lied about the sex of the shooter because that's what the shooter would have wanted.”

title: ‘Victim of misogyny’: Macpherson mocks Clare O’Neill’s defence of Sussan Ley
description: Sky News host James Macpherson criticises Labor MP Clare O’Neill over her comments on the change in Liberal leadership.  “Clare O'Neill is busy posting videos from the comfort of HER home about the Liberal leadership,” Mr Macpherson said.  “Clare O'Neill is wondering whether Sussan Ley was the victim of misogyny.  “I'm impressed that a Labor MP suddenly knows the difference between males and females.  “According to Clare O'Neill, when men said that the Opposition wasn't strong, what they were really saying was that Sussan Ley was a woman.  “Maybe Sussan Ley got more respect from the Labor side of politics than from her own colleagues because Labor quite liked the fact that Sussan Ley was polling at just 18 per cent.”

title: ‘Abundantly clear’: No ‘love lost’ between Sussan Ley and Angus Taylor
description: Sky News host James Macpherson says there was no “love lost” between Liberal Leader Angus Taylor and former Liberal leader Sussan Ley.  “Is there a danger David Littleproud’s comments today about Sussan Ley risk making him look a little two-faced,” Mr Macpherson said.  “It was unnecessary wasn’t it.”

title: ‘We are very passionate’: Anne Webster on Nationals in Coalition
description: Nationals MP Anne Webster sits down with Sky News host James Macpherson to analyse the National Party in the Coalition.  “We are a different party,” Ms Webster said.  “We are very passionate … because our people … are incredibly important to us.”

title: ‘Progressives warn’ against Trump turning US into ‘dictatorship’ as Keir Starmer destroys UK
description: Sky News host James Macpherson analyses UK PM Keir Starmer cancelling local government elections.  Mr Macpherson sat down with GB News host Alex Armstrong to go over the issue in the UK.  “Why is Keir Starmer cancelling local elections?”

title: Turnbull ridiculed after branding Taylor a ‘qualified idiot’
description: The Australian Associate Editor Graham Lloyd warns Malcolm Turnbull he risks diminishing his own influence with continued attacks on Opposition Leader Angus Taylor.  “I think the more Malcom Turnbull carries on like this, the more his currency’s devalued,” Mr Lloyd told Sky News host James Macpherson.  “This reflects his frustration at his own outcomes.  “People will start to switch off.”

title: Angus Taylor’s new polling results analysed
description: Sky News host Paul Murray analyses updated polling results surrounding the main players in the fight for parliament.

title: ‘Thus the Coalition, thus the Opposition’: Angus Taylor’s new position analysed
description: On tonight’s episode of Paul Murray Live, Sky News host Paul Murray discusses Angus Taylor’s new role as Liberal Leader, cost of living, US politics and more.

title: ‘What the Liberal Party will stand for’: Taylor pledges reset for Opposition
description: Sky News host Paul Murray analyses Liberal Leader Angus Taylor placing ‘Australian values’ art the centre of democracy.

title: ‘The One Nation phenomenon’: Pauline Hanson’s party sees intense growth
description: Sky News host Paul Murray highlights the “One Nation phenomenon” and how the polling results are changing in the new political climate.

title: ‘Hammer blow’: Trump 'destroys' Obama-era climate agenda
description: The Australian Associate Editor Graham Lloyd explains how US President Donald Trump is systematically unwinding green policies introduced under Barack Obama.  “There has never been a political consensus in the United States to take actions on climate change,” Mr Lloyd told Sky News host James Macpherson.  “Trump is going about the business of destroying the green industrial complex.  “He’s out of the Paris agreement, he’s withdrawn the US from the United Nations framework on climate change, and now he’s removing the underpinning legislation in the US that drives domestic action there.   “It’s a hammer blow to all those ambitions of Barack Obama.”

title: ‘I’m here to fight’: Jacinta Price vows to ‘protect the Australian way of life’
description: Liberal Senator Jacinta Nampijinpa Price claims the Liberals new focus will be on protecting the Australian way of life.   “I’m here to fight for the benefit of the Australian people,” Ms Price told Sky News host Paul Murray.  “Fundamentally, we need to lift the living standards of the Australian people.  “We need to protect our way of life.”

title: ‘You’re a has-been’: Jacinta Price tells Turnbull to ‘zip it’
description: Liberal Senator Jacinta Nampijinpa Price delivers blow to former prime minister Malcolm Turnbull.  “I tell you what, who needs to zip their lips though, Malcolm Turnbull,” Ms Price told Sky News host Paul Murray.  “You’re done, you’re dusted, you’re a has-been.  “We don’t want to hear your ramblings anymore.”

title: Reform UK takes Keir Starmer’s government to High Court over election cancellations
description: GB News host Alex Armstrong analyse Reform UK taking the UK government to the High Court over cancelling elections.  “This is escalating quite quickly,” Mr Armstrong said.  “Funnily enough they were cancelled again because the government has these devolution plans.”

title: One Nation draws level with the Coalition in new polling
description: The battle is on for Australia’s conservative vote as One Nation draws level with the Coalition in new polling out today.  According to the latest Resolve Political Monitor in Nine Newspapers, both One Nation and the Coalition are level on 23 per cent.  In terms of net likeability, Angus Taylor also secured a plus three percentage point rating, compared to a minus twelve rating for Anthony Albanese.
